WEBVTT

00:18.252 --> 00:20.321
[CRASH, SHATTER]

00:22.156 --> 00:24.558
AAH! HE'S GOT DR. ZOLA!

00:24.625 --> 00:27.027
AAH! HELP ME!

00:27.095 --> 00:28.796
[YELLING]

00:35.436 --> 00:36.504
* WHAT'S NEW, SCOOBY-DOO? *

00:36.570 --> 00:38.206
* WE'RE COMING AFTER YOU *

00:38.272 --> 00:41.008
* WE'RE GONNA SOLVE
THAT MYSTERY *

00:41.075 --> 00:42.176
* I SEE YOU, SCOOBY-DOO *

00:42.243 --> 00:44.044
* THE TRAIL
LEADS BACK TO YOU *

00:44.112 --> 00:46.947
* WHAT'S NEW, SCOOBY-DOO? *

00:47.014 --> 00:48.249
* WHAT'S NEW, SCOOBY-DOO? *

00:48.316 --> 00:50.050
* WE'RE GONNA FOLLOW YOU *

00:50.118 --> 00:52.786
* YOU'RE GONNA SOLVE
THAT MYSTERY *

00:52.853 --> 00:54.054
* WE SEE YOU, SCOOBY-DOO *

00:54.122 --> 00:55.856
* WE'RE COMING AFTER YOU *

00:55.923 --> 00:58.826
* WHAT'S NEW, SCOOBY-DOO? *

01:00.794 --> 01:02.096
* DON'T LOOK BACK *

01:02.163 --> 01:06.300
* YOU MAY FIND
ANOTHER CLUE *

01:06.367 --> 01:11.071
* SCOOBY SNAX WILL BE
WAITING HERE FOR YOU *

01:11.139 --> 01:12.206
* WHAT'S NEW, SCOOBY-DOO? *

01:12.273 --> 01:13.707
* WE'RE COMING AFTER YOU *

01:13.774 --> 01:16.510
* WE'RE GONNA SOLVE
THAT MYSTERY *

01:16.577 --> 01:18.045
* I SEE YOU, SCOOBY-DOO *

01:18.112 --> 01:19.580
* THE TRAIL
LEADS BACK TO YOU *

01:19.647 --> 01:22.350
* WHAT'S NEW, SCOOBY-DOO? *

01:22.416 --> 01:24.017
* NA-NA NA-NA NA *

01:24.084 --> 01:25.419
* NA-NA NA-NA NA *

01:25.486 --> 01:28.322
* NA-NA NA NA NA-NA NA *

01:28.389 --> 01:31.559
* NA-NA NA-NA NA
NA-NA NA-NA NA *

01:31.625 --> 01:34.662
* WHAT'S NEW, SCOOBY-DOO? *

01:38.031 --> 01:39.300
VOLUNTEER WORK
AT THE ZOO.

01:39.367 --> 01:41.335
WHAT A GREAT JOB
FOR SHAGGY.

01:41.402 --> 01:43.504
EXCEPT WE HAVEN'T
SEEN HIM SINCE
WE GOT HERE.

01:43.571 --> 01:47.107
MY GUESS
IS VOLUNTEER LUNCH BREAK
HAS NO TIME LIMIT.

01:47.175 --> 01:49.510
Shabby: LIKE, GANG, HEY!
HA HA HA!

01:49.577 --> 01:51.912
I'M UP HERE!
THIS IS TOOTS.

01:51.979 --> 01:53.814
SHE LOVES PEANUTS,

01:53.881 --> 01:55.249
AND, COINCIDENTALLY,
SO DO I.

01:55.316 --> 01:57.251
2 FOR YOU, 1 FOR ME.

01:57.318 --> 01:59.353
2 FOR YOU, 1 FOR ME.

01:59.420 --> 02:01.722
AND SHE ALSO LOVES
ELEPHANT JOKES. WATCH.

02:01.789 --> 02:04.158
HOW DO YOU MAKE
AN ELEPHANT FLOAT?

02:04.225 --> 02:05.626
JUST ADD ICE CREAM.

02:05.693 --> 02:07.094
[TRUMPETING]

02:07.161 --> 02:08.229
SEE?

02:08.296 --> 02:10.998
FLOAT? ICE CREAM?

02:11.064 --> 02:13.467
OH, I GET IT--

02:13.534 --> 02:14.468
HEE HEE HEE.

02:14.535 --> 02:16.970
THAT'S SCOOBY'S NEW PAL,
LITTLE PETE.

02:17.037 --> 02:19.773
WHAT A CUTIE. IS HE NEW HERE?

02:19.840 --> 02:21.008
HE WAS FOUND
IN THE WILD,

02:21.074 --> 02:23.644
AND THEY'VE BEEN
CARING FOR HIM
IN THE ZOO NURSERY.

02:26.414 --> 02:28.148
OH, THERE'S LITTLE PETE.

02:28.216 --> 02:30.618
I KNEW HE'D BE
OUT HERE WITH SCOOBY.

02:30.684 --> 02:33.053
ZELLA THE ZOOKEEPER,
MEET MY PALS.

02:33.120 --> 02:34.655
TIME FOR ANOTHER
LUNCH BREAK?

02:34.722 --> 02:36.357
SURE, IF YOU'D LIKE.

02:36.424 --> 02:39.427
BUT I NEED TO GET
LITTLE PETE READY
FOR HIS FLIGHT.

02:39.493 --> 02:41.595
I THOUGHT PENGUINS
WERE FLIGHTLESS BIRDS.

02:41.662 --> 02:44.565
YES, THEY ARE.
BUT IT'S TIME
FOR THIS PENGUIN

02:44.632 --> 02:47.368
TO GO BACK
TO HIS FAMILY
IN ANTARCTICA.

02:47.435 --> 02:50.438
ANTARCTICA? YOU MEAN
THE ONE IN THE SOUTH POLE?

02:50.504 --> 02:51.939
BUT THAT'S SO FAR AWAY,

02:52.005 --> 02:55.576
AND SCOOBY'S BEEN TAKING
REALLY GOOD CARE OF HIM HERE.

02:55.643 --> 02:56.844
[BELCH]

02:56.910 --> 02:58.078
OH...

02:58.145 --> 02:59.580
I'M AFRAID IT'S FOR
HIS OWN WELFARE.

02:59.647 --> 03:03.183
HE NEEDS TO BE BACK
IN HIS NATURAL
CLIMATE.

03:03.251 --> 03:05.486
BUT...TELL YOU WHAT.

03:05.553 --> 03:07.855
SEEING AS SCOOBY'S
BEEN SUCH A GOOD UNCLE

03:07.921 --> 03:10.658
AND SHAGGY'S SO GOOD
AT TAKING CARE
OF ANIMALS,

03:10.724 --> 03:13.994
HOW WOULD YOU GUYS
LIKE TO ACCOMPANY
LITTLE PETE

03:14.061 --> 03:16.230
ON THE TRIP BACK HOME?

03:17.365 --> 03:19.267
I'LL TAKE THAT
AS A YES.

03:20.568 --> 03:23.337
Fred: HEY, SHAGGY,
THANKS FOR ASKING
THE ZOOKEEPER

03:23.404 --> 03:25.373
IF WE COULD COME
WITH YOU TO ANTARCTICA.

03:25.439 --> 03:27.107
LIKE, THE TRIP
WOULDN'T BE A TRIP

03:27.174 --> 03:28.709
WITHOUT YOU GUYS ALONG.

03:28.776 --> 03:31.078
GUESS SCOOB'S GOT
HIS JOB CUT OUT, HUH,

03:31.144 --> 03:33.614
KEEPING LITTLE PETE
FROM GETTIN' BORED.

03:35.683 --> 03:36.817
[GASP]

03:40.321 --> 03:41.722
[HISS]

03:58.272 --> 04:00.140
HEY, COLD ENOUGH
FOR YA?

04:00.207 --> 04:03.644
LIKE, THANKS, CAPTAIN.
IT'S NICE AND CHILLY
FOR THE LITTLE GUY.

04:03.711 --> 04:05.979
I WOULDN'T HAVE IT
ANY OTHER WAY.

04:06.046 --> 04:07.315
LOVE THE COLD.

04:07.381 --> 04:10.318
IN FACT,
I'M A DEDICATED ICEIST.

04:10.384 --> 04:12.320
AND AN ICEIST IS...

04:12.386 --> 04:14.322
SOMEONE
WHO CHEWS ICE?

04:14.388 --> 04:15.789
ONLY ON SPECIAL
HOLIDAYS.

04:15.856 --> 04:19.059
WE DEVOTE OUR LIVES
TO THE LOVE OF
FROZEN WATER.

04:19.126 --> 04:21.061
IT'S A DEPLETING
RESOURCE, YOU KNOW.

04:21.128 --> 04:22.496
IN A MILLION YEARS
OR SO,

04:22.563 --> 04:24.332
THIS WILL BE
AN ICELESS PLANET!

04:24.398 --> 04:26.467
AND THEN WHAT
WILL WE DO?

04:26.534 --> 04:28.268
I NEVER LIKE TO PLAN
THAT FAR AHEAD.

04:28.336 --> 04:29.637
THAT'S WHY I FLY
THESE RUNS

04:29.703 --> 04:31.739
TO THE EVENTUALLY
MELTING SOUTH POLE.

04:31.805 --> 04:33.541
GOTTA ENJOY ICE
WHILE YOU GOT IT.

04:33.607 --> 04:35.242
BY THE WAY,
I DON'T MEAN TO PRY,

04:35.309 --> 04:37.044
BUT WHO'S FLYING
THE PLANE?

04:37.110 --> 04:38.412
WE'RE ON
AUTOMATIC PILOT.

04:38.479 --> 04:40.414
THIS BABY PRACTICALLY
FLIES ITSELF.

04:40.481 --> 04:42.215
WANT A TURN
BEHIND THE WHEEL?

04:42.282 --> 04:45.519
SURE! I PRIDE MYSELF
ON MY DRIVING SKILLS.

04:45.586 --> 04:47.755
REFASTEN
YOUR SEAT BELTS.

04:47.821 --> 04:49.289
[ENGINE RUMBLES]

04:49.357 --> 04:52.292
Fred:
WHAT'S THIS THING
DO-OAAAH!

04:57.030 --> 05:01.835
THIS IS A PIECE
OF CAAAAAKE!

05:01.902 --> 05:03.804
Captain:
CAPE DART WAY STATION,

05:03.871 --> 05:06.674
BUILT ON AN ACRE
OF PRIME ICE ESTATE.

05:06.740 --> 05:09.810
NEAREST NEIGHBOR
HASN'T BEEN SEEN
IN AN ICE AGE.

05:09.877 --> 05:11.445
Daphne: I DON'T SEE
ANY PENGUINS YET.

05:11.512 --> 05:13.947
I DON'T SEE
MUCH OF ANYTHING.
IT'S SO DARK OUT.

05:14.014 --> 05:15.282
WHAT TIME IS MORNING?

05:15.349 --> 05:16.617
JULY.

05:16.684 --> 05:19.019
UNTIL THEN,
IT'S CONTINUAL NIGHT.

05:19.086 --> 05:22.022
Shaggy: MAN, WHAT A GREAT
PLACE FOR SLEEPIN' IN!

05:26.026 --> 05:28.161
LOOKS LIKE
THEY WEREN'T
EXPECTING GUESTS.

05:28.228 --> 05:31.399
NO, NO. THIS PLACE
WAS UP AND RUNNING
JUST LAST WEEK.

05:31.465 --> 05:34.301
THERE WAS EQUIPMENT
HERE AND...WORKERS.

05:34.368 --> 05:36.670
SOMETHING'S
TERRIBLY WRONG.

05:36.737 --> 05:39.607
I'LL SAY.
LOOK OVER THERE!

05:42.376 --> 05:43.677
HE'S IN SHOCK.

05:43.744 --> 05:45.679
SOMETHING MUST HAVE
REALLY SCARED HIM.

05:45.746 --> 05:49.049
LIKE, MAYBE
HE'S THE GUY WHO HAS
TO CLEAN UP THIS PLACE.

05:55.689 --> 05:56.990
AAH!

05:57.057 --> 05:59.393
THAT THING!
THAT THING!

05:59.460 --> 06:01.695
EASY, EASY!
YOU'RE SAFE NOW.

06:03.196 --> 06:06.066
AAH!

06:06.133 --> 06:10.237
MAYBE IT IS US.
THOSE HOODS DO SCARY
THINGS WITH YOUR HAIR.

06:10.303 --> 06:12.239
PLEASE, TRY TO RELAX.

06:12.305 --> 06:14.542
CAN YOU TELL US
WHO YOU ARE?

06:14.608 --> 06:16.209
MONROE...HOPPER.

06:16.276 --> 06:18.345
ASSISTANT TO
DR. ARMAND ZOLA.

06:18.412 --> 06:19.312
AND WHO'S THAT?

06:19.379 --> 06:20.714
EEE!

06:20.781 --> 06:22.950
FORGIVE ME. I'VE BEEN
THROUGH QUITE AN ORDEAL.

06:23.016 --> 06:24.785
WOULD YOU LIKE TO
TELL US ABOUT IT?

06:24.852 --> 06:26.520
NO, NO, NO!

06:26.587 --> 06:29.122
BUT I HAVE TO.
YOU MUST BE WARNED.

06:29.189 --> 06:30.891
DR. ZOLA'S
A BRILLIANT SCIENTIST

06:30.958 --> 06:32.626
WITH THE ANSWERS
TO GLOBAL WARMING,

06:32.693 --> 06:36.029
THE SHRINKING OZONE,
THE THREAT TO
POLAR WILDLIFE!

06:36.096 --> 06:38.499
AMAZING!
WHERE IS THIS MAN?

06:38.566 --> 06:42.503
THAT'S THE HORRIBLE PART.
A GIANT CREATURE
SLITHERED OUT OF THE SEA,

06:42.570 --> 06:46.173
PART HUMAN
AND PART HIDEOUS, SCALY,
KNIFE-TOOTHED FISH MONSTER!

06:46.239 --> 06:49.242
IT DEMOLISHED THIS PLACE
AND DRAGGED OUT DR. ZOLA,

06:49.309 --> 06:53.213
PLUNGING HIM DOWN,
DOWN INTO THE FREEZING
WATERS BELOW US.

06:53.280 --> 06:55.716
PETEY WANTS TO GO
HOME!

06:55.783 --> 06:58.719
THE WORKERS
RAN FOR THEIR LIVES,
BUT I COULDN'T MOVE!

06:58.786 --> 07:01.889
NUMB WITH FEAR,
SEEING POOR DR. ZOLA...

07:01.955 --> 07:03.724
NO...NO!

07:03.791 --> 07:06.994
RELAX, MR. HOPPER!
IT'S ALL OVER NOW.

07:07.060 --> 07:08.128
EE!

07:08.195 --> 07:09.563
OR NOT.

07:09.630 --> 07:12.199
THE GENERATOR!
SOMEHOW IT'S WORKING AGAIN!

07:12.265 --> 07:13.634
WHERE'S
THE GENERATOR?

07:13.701 --> 07:16.136
OUT THERE
IN THE GENERATOR ROOM.

07:16.203 --> 07:17.571
NOW, THAT'S GREAT
PLANNING.

07:18.872 --> 07:20.107
WHAT'S THAT?

07:20.173 --> 07:21.709
Fred: HALT!
WHO GOES THERE?

07:21.775 --> 07:24.144
I--I MEAN,
WHO'S ALREADY HERE?

07:26.847 --> 07:28.916
ZOINKS! IT'S ANOTHER
CREATURE!

07:28.982 --> 07:31.752
IT'S JUST A PERSON
IN A DIVING SUIT.

07:31.819 --> 07:34.688
WHY WOULD ANYONE BE
WEARING A DIVING SUIT
INDOORS?

07:35.789 --> 07:37.390
BECAUSE I'M FREEZING.

07:37.457 --> 07:39.426
I DESIGNED THIS SUIT
TO WITHSTAND COLD

07:39.493 --> 07:41.294
HUNDREDS OF DEGREES
BELOW ZERO.

07:41.361 --> 07:43.196
WHO ARE YOU ANYWAY?

07:43.263 --> 07:45.432
WE CAME TO BRING
A PENGUIN BACK TO THE WILD.

07:45.499 --> 07:47.000
YOU SHOULD HAVE
STAYED INSIDE.

07:47.067 --> 07:49.036
HAVE YOU NOTICED
IT'S REALLY COLD HERE

07:49.102 --> 07:50.470
SINCE THE GENERATOR
WAS WRECKED?

07:50.538 --> 07:51.972
BUT NOW IT'S ON AGAIN.

07:52.039 --> 07:54.608
THAT'S MY JOB.
I'M SERGEANT LINDA RAUCH

07:54.675 --> 07:56.510
FROM THE ARMY CORPS
OF ENGINEERS,

07:56.577 --> 07:59.547
ASSIGNED TO THIS...
BLEAK, CHILLING PLACE.

07:59.613 --> 08:02.249
I GUESS WE OWE YOU
SOME THANKS FOR THE REPAIRS.

08:02.315 --> 08:03.751
YOU DON'T OWE ME
ANYTHING...

08:03.817 --> 08:06.920
UNLESS YOU CAN ARRANGE
FOR A TRANSFER
TO MAUI.

08:06.987 --> 08:08.488
BRR!

08:13.326 --> 08:16.830
Fred: WE'D BETTER GET
THIS LITTLE PENGUIN
BACK TO PENGUINVILLE.

08:21.802 --> 08:23.804
ACCORDING TO THE ZOOKEEPER'S
INFORMATION,

08:23.871 --> 08:27.340
THE PENGUIN POPULATION
SHOULD BE RIGHT WHERE
THESE BUILDINGS ARE!

08:27.407 --> 08:30.978
INNOCENT PENGUINS
DISPLACED BY A GROSS
MISUSE OF ICE!

08:31.044 --> 08:34.548
I TELL PEOPLE NOT TO BUILD
ON THE ICE FIELD,
BUT DO THEY LISTEN?

08:34.615 --> 08:38.752
I NEED TO PREP MY PROPS
AND FLY YOU ICEBREAKERS
OUTTA HERE.

08:40.187 --> 08:42.022
HMM. SEEMS LIKE
SHE WOULDN'T MIND

08:42.089 --> 08:44.892
SEEING THE WHOLE
WAY STATION GO AWAY.

08:44.958 --> 08:46.794
HOW DO WE FIND
THE PENGUINS?

08:46.860 --> 08:49.963
EASY. LOOK FOR TUXEDOS,
AND IF THEY'RE ON BIRDS,

08:50.030 --> 08:51.531
THAT'S THEM.

08:57.337 --> 08:58.839
[TEETH CHATTERING]

09:00.841 --> 09:03.010
NO SIGN YET
OF LITTLE PETE'S COLONY.

09:03.076 --> 09:06.279
GOOD THING YOU BROUGHT ALONG
THOSE NIGHT-VISION BINOCULARS.

09:06.346 --> 09:07.815
IT'S 3 MORE MONTHS
TILL MORNING.

09:07.881 --> 09:10.017
UH...WHAT HAS GILLS
AND SCALES

09:10.083 --> 09:12.653
AND RUNS LIKE
A MAN, BUT LOOKS
LIKE A SHARK?

09:12.720 --> 09:14.622
DAPHNE THIS IS NO TIME
FOR A RIDDLE.

09:14.688 --> 09:17.557
NO! I REALLY SEE IT!
LOOK!

09:18.759 --> 09:21.695
JINKIES!
IT'S THAT FINNED FIEND!

09:21.762 --> 09:22.863
WHAT DO WE DO?

09:22.930 --> 09:25.232
HOW ABOUT
NOT JUST STAND HERE?!

09:25.298 --> 09:27.267
SPLIT UP, GANG,
AND RUN!

09:30.270 --> 09:31.639
RRRR!

09:32.439 --> 09:33.373
YIKES!

09:33.440 --> 09:35.676
HANG ON, SHAGGY!

09:35.743 --> 09:38.278
BUT IT'S HANGING ON
TO ME!

09:39.947 --> 09:41.081
UNH!

09:42.082 --> 09:43.516
RRRR!

09:43.583 --> 09:45.753
THAT THING'S
GOT FRED!

09:52.660 --> 09:54.127
RRRR!

09:54.194 --> 09:54.995
RRRR!

09:55.062 --> 09:57.464
FREDDY!
WE CAN'T GET TO HIM!

09:57.530 --> 09:59.800
I WONDER...

10:07.207 --> 10:09.710
YAY!
YAY!
YAY!

10:10.844 --> 10:12.646
AAH!
AAH!
AAH!

10:12.713 --> 10:14.014
RRRRR!

10:14.081 --> 10:16.650
OHHHH!

10:23.590 --> 10:25.392
BON VOYAGE!

10:28.662 --> 10:30.230
ZOINKS!
WHAT'S THAT?!

10:31.598 --> 10:32.733
[TEETH
CHATTERING]

10:32.800 --> 10:35.435
THERE'S A MAN
UNDER THE ICE.

10:35.502 --> 10:37.838
[ENGINE REVVING]

10:38.672 --> 10:39.840
AAH!

10:39.907 --> 10:41.842
I WISH YOU WOULDN'T
KEEP DOING THAT.

10:41.909 --> 10:44.077
IT'S DR. ZOLA,
FROZEN SOLID!

10:44.144 --> 10:48.048
MAN, HE MUST BE COLD
WITHOUT HIS EARMUFFS.

10:48.115 --> 10:50.083
Daphne: DO YOU THINK
HE CAN BE REVIVED?

10:50.150 --> 10:53.120
WE MUST! HE HAS SO MUCH
TO OFFER THE HUMAN RACE!

10:53.186 --> 10:55.088
HE COULD EVEN TELL YOU
WHERE THE PENGUINS WENT.

10:55.155 --> 10:57.224
HE'S GOT TO BE
THAWED OUT QUICKLY.

10:57.290 --> 11:00.160
LIKE, DOES ANYONE HERE
HAVE A BLOW DRYER?

11:00.227 --> 11:01.228
WHAT COLOR?

11:01.294 --> 11:02.595
NOT TOO QUICKLY.

11:02.662 --> 11:04.932
THE SUDDEN RISE
IN TEMPERATURE
COULD THREATEN HIS LIFE.

11:04.998 --> 11:06.366
WELL, BEING FROZEN
LIKE LEFTOVERS

11:06.433 --> 11:08.736
COULDN'T BE REAL GOOD
FOR HIS HEALTH EITHER.

11:08.802 --> 11:10.838
GOOD POINT. THAT'S WHY
I'M GOING TO THAW OUT

11:10.904 --> 11:12.505
IN MY TANNING BOOTH.

11:12.572 --> 11:16.844
HMM. SEEMS LIKE SHE'D
DO ANYTHING TO GET OUT
OF THIS PLACE.

11:16.910 --> 11:19.279
I MADE SOME TEA
TO WARM US UP.

11:19.346 --> 11:21.514
HEY.
AAH!

11:21.581 --> 11:24.985
LISTEN UP, I'VE GOT
SOME BAD NEWS
AND SOME GOOD NEWS.

11:25.052 --> 11:28.621
THE BAD NEWS IS
I WON'T BE FLYING YOU
OUT OF HERE FOR 2 DAYS.

11:28.688 --> 11:31.058
THERE'S A BIG HAIL STORM
COMING.

11:31.124 --> 11:34.227
OH, NO!
HAIL STORMS MAKE
ME REALLY NERVOUS!

11:34.294 --> 11:35.228
WHAT DOESN'T?

11:35.295 --> 11:36.629
WHAT'S THE GOOD NEWS?

11:36.696 --> 11:38.431
HAIL IS ICE!

11:38.498 --> 11:39.432
GREAT!

11:39.499 --> 11:41.101
WELL, WE HAVE 2 DAYS.

11:41.168 --> 11:44.104
LET'S GET LITTLE PETE
TO HIS, UH, PEOPLE

11:44.171 --> 11:47.374
BEFORE THAT
AMPHIBIOUS ABNORMALITY
FINDS ITS WAY BACK.

11:47.440 --> 11:49.810
[TEETH CHATTERING]

11:49.877 --> 11:51.344
[HAIR DRYER
BLOWING]

11:56.283 --> 11:58.051
Shaggy: THE TV HERE
IS JUST LIKE THE WEATHER.

11:58.118 --> 12:00.553
ALL YOU GET IS SNOW.
HA HA!

12:00.620 --> 12:03.323
RRRRR!

12:03.390 --> 12:05.325
Shaggy: HEY! LIKE,
WHO TURNED OUT THE LIGHT?!

12:06.326 --> 12:08.095
THE HEAT'S OFF, TOO.

12:08.161 --> 12:09.262
NO HEAT?

12:09.329 --> 12:10.330
BUT MELTING THE ICE

12:10.397 --> 12:12.365
WAS OUR ONLY CHANCE
TO REVIVE DR. ZOLA.

12:12.432 --> 12:15.168
THAT ENGINEER,
SERGEANT LINDA,
CONTROLS THE POWER.

12:15.235 --> 12:17.004
COULD SHE HAVE
SOMETHING TO DO

12:17.070 --> 12:18.305
WITH THE FISH-FACED
FELON?

12:18.371 --> 12:20.607
WE BETTER GO CHECK OUT
THE GENERATOR ROOM.

12:20.673 --> 12:22.209
CAN YOU STAY
AND WATCH DR. ZOLA?

12:22.275 --> 12:24.344
I WOULD NEVER
LEAVE HIS SIDE.

12:27.347 --> 12:28.982
THERE HE GOES.

12:30.350 --> 12:32.752
ALL RIGHT, WE NEED
TO SPLIT UP AGAIN.

12:32.820 --> 12:35.188
SOME OF US NEED
TO GO SEARCH
THAT COASTLINE,

12:35.255 --> 12:37.757
AND SOME OF US
SHOULD KEEP WATCH
HERE AT THE ICE FIELD.

12:37.825 --> 12:41.128
SHAGGY, THIS TIME
YOU AND SCOOBY
GET TO CHOOSE.

12:41.194 --> 12:45.065
LET'S SEE, THE COASTLINE
IS WHERE DAPHNE
JUST SAW THE MONSTER.

12:45.132 --> 12:46.066
YEAH.

12:46.133 --> 12:47.567
BUT WHEN WE STAY BEHIND,

12:47.634 --> 12:49.136
THE MONSTER
ALWAYS FINDS US.

12:49.202 --> 12:50.503
YEAH.

12:50.570 --> 12:53.640
ON THE OTHER HAND,
THE MONSTER ALWAYS
FINDS US ANYWAY.

12:53.706 --> 12:55.175
YEAH.

12:55.242 --> 12:56.276
PICK IT ALREADY!

12:56.343 --> 12:58.211
AAH!
AAH!

12:58.278 --> 12:59.646
RRRRR!

12:59.712 --> 13:01.648
NOT THIS TIME,
FELLA!

13:01.714 --> 13:03.350
ARGH!

13:03.416 --> 13:05.552
OOH! RRR!

13:05.618 --> 13:07.320
[WHIMPERING]

13:07.387 --> 13:09.322
OOH-OOH-OOH!

13:09.389 --> 13:12.993
NO! NO!
SAVE SCOOBY!

13:16.329 --> 13:17.397
YOU CAN'T, SHAGGY!

13:17.464 --> 13:19.132
THE WATER'S TOO COLD!
YOU'LL FREEZE!

13:19.199 --> 13:21.935
BUT WHAT ABOUT
SCOOBY?!

13:35.715 --> 13:37.750
SCOOBY!
THERE'S NO TIME!

13:37.817 --> 13:39.752
WE'VE GOT TO SAVE
SCOOBY NOW

13:39.819 --> 13:42.055
BEFORE THE GILLED GHOUL
GRABS HIM!

13:42.122 --> 13:44.257
I'LL FIND THAT
SUB-ZERO DIVING SUIT!

13:44.324 --> 13:48.061
LITTLE PETE! NO!

13:48.128 --> 13:50.797
IT'S OK. HIS FEATHERS
PROTECT HIM
FROM THE COLD.

13:50.864 --> 13:54.501
YEAH, BUT, LIKE,
WHAT'S GONNA PROTECT HIM
FROM THE MONSTER?!

14:18.325 --> 14:19.459
OHH!

14:19.526 --> 14:21.428
AAH!

14:30.637 --> 14:31.939
[GASP]

14:35.775 --> 14:37.344
[SHIVERING]

14:37.410 --> 14:39.712
IS THIS SOME KIND
OF AIR HOSE?

14:39.779 --> 14:41.214
HMM.

14:41.281 --> 14:42.649
AW...[KISS]

14:43.650 --> 14:45.518
M--M--MY HERO!

14:47.287 --> 14:49.289
Daphne:
WE'LL NEVER GET LITTLE PETE
BACK TO HIS PENGUINS

14:49.356 --> 14:51.591
WHILE THAT SCALY SCOUNDREL'S
STILL SKULKING.

14:51.658 --> 14:55.162
NEEDLESS HOLES BROKEN
THROUGH THE PRECIOUS
POLAR SURFACE.

14:55.228 --> 14:57.364
ICE DOESN'T GROW
ON TREES, YOU KNOW?

14:57.430 --> 14:59.166
[CRYING]

14:59.232 --> 15:00.600
UNLESS YOU COUNT ICICLES.

15:00.667 --> 15:01.935
I CAN'T WAIT TO CART

15:02.002 --> 15:04.837
ALL YOU ICY-HEARTED
ICE-HACKERS OUT OF HERE!

15:04.904 --> 15:06.239
I CAN'T WAIT TO GO.

15:06.306 --> 15:09.442
I'M ALREADY IN TRAINING
FOR THE MAUI TRIATHLON.

15:09.509 --> 15:10.710
UNH!

15:10.777 --> 15:12.112
[BLOWING OUT]

15:12.179 --> 15:13.446
UNH!

15:13.513 --> 15:16.083
AH, THAT'S A GOOD GOAL.

15:16.149 --> 15:19.686
I'M TRAINING
TO BENCH 220...1.

15:19.752 --> 15:21.221
DR. ZOLA'S
A BRILLIANT MAN.

15:21.288 --> 15:24.391
HE KNEW WHEN
DISASTER WOULD REAR
ITS DISASTROUS HEAD.

15:24.457 --> 15:25.792
WHAT
DO YOU MEAN?

15:25.858 --> 15:27.394
THE LAST TIME I CAME HERE,

15:27.460 --> 15:29.896
HE WARNED EVERYONE
IN THE PLACE TO TAKE
MY NEXT FLIGHT OUT

15:29.963 --> 15:32.465
OR THEY'D SUFFER
HORRENDOUS CONSEQUENCES.

15:32.532 --> 15:34.001
AGAIN, HMM.

15:34.067 --> 15:37.670
SUSPECTS AND CLUES
SEEM TO BE SWIMMING
THROUGH HERE LIKE MINNOWS.

15:37.737 --> 15:41.374
THEN THE TIME HAS COME
FOR US TO TACKLE
THAT BIG FISH.

15:45.178 --> 15:47.747
WELL, GANG, WE'RE GOIN'
FOR THE PRIZE CATCH.

15:47.814 --> 15:49.649
WE'VE GOT A FLEXIBLE
ALUMINUM POLE,

15:49.716 --> 15:51.251
PRECISION REEL,

15:51.318 --> 15:52.385
STEEL WIRE
CABLE LINE,

15:52.452 --> 15:53.386
AND OF COURSE...

15:53.453 --> 15:54.587
LIVE BAIT.

15:54.654 --> 15:57.490
IN FACT, THE LIVE BAITIEST
WE'VE EVER BEEN.

15:57.557 --> 15:58.358
DON'T WORRY, GUYS.

15:58.425 --> 15:59.826
AS SOON AS
THE CREATURE SHOWS

15:59.892 --> 16:01.594
TO GOBBLE UP
YOU TASTY MORSELS,

16:01.661 --> 16:04.297
WE SNAG HIM WITH THIS VELCRO
SURE-TO-STICK NET.

16:04.364 --> 16:06.266
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT'S WORSE.

16:06.333 --> 16:09.469
DANGLING HERE TO ATTRACT
A TERRIFYING, FEROCIOUS
SEA FREAK,

16:09.536 --> 16:12.872
OR SPRAYING OURSELVES
IN SCENT OF SQUID.

16:12.939 --> 16:14.374
P.U.!

16:14.441 --> 16:17.577
Fred: WHOA!
THEY'RE BITING TODAY!

16:17.644 --> 16:19.679
I SEE SOMETHING COMING
UNDER THE ICE.

16:19.746 --> 16:21.514
SEAL! PULL THEM UP!

16:25.685 --> 16:27.520
GO AWAY! GO AWAY!

16:27.587 --> 16:29.056
WE'RE NOT REALLY FISH!

16:29.122 --> 16:30.857
SCOOB, BARK
OR SOMETHING.

16:30.923 --> 16:32.492
HUH?

16:33.993 --> 16:37.764
[BARKING
LIKE A SEAL]

16:39.466 --> 16:41.601
[BARKING]

16:46.806 --> 16:48.108
HANG IN THERE, GUYS!

16:48.175 --> 16:50.577
A GOOD FISHERMAN
IS ALWAYS PATIENT.

16:50.643 --> 16:52.045
[CHATTERING]

16:55.248 --> 16:59.086
FRED, I THINK
THE BLOOD IS RUNNING
TO OUR TAIL FINS!

16:59.152 --> 17:01.554
REMEMBER, PATIENCE
IS ITS OWN REWARD.

17:01.621 --> 17:04.391
MAYBE SO,
BUT SCOOBY SNAX ARE OURS,

17:04.457 --> 17:07.727
PLUS A HOT BATH
IN THE SOMEWHAT NEAR FUTURE.

17:07.794 --> 17:09.262
OH, OH, PLEASE!

17:11.898 --> 17:13.533
[CREATURE GROWLING]

17:14.967 --> 17:16.436
THE CREATURE!

17:16.503 --> 17:17.270
RUN!

17:17.337 --> 17:19.572
* IT'S ALL THE SAME *

17:19.639 --> 17:22.342
* SAME OLD TOWN
WITH A DIFFERENT NAME *

17:22.409 --> 17:24.311
* THAT'S FINE BY ME *

17:24.377 --> 17:27.747
* THERE'S ONLY ONE PLACE
THAT I WANT TO BE *

17:27.814 --> 17:29.716
* SOUTHBOUND ON I-5 *

17:29.782 --> 17:33.019
* WINDOWS DOWN AND MUSIC
ON THE STEREO *

17:33.086 --> 17:34.687
* I'M DRIVIN',
AND I'M DREAMIN' *

17:34.754 --> 17:37.890
* THERE'S NO PLACE
I'D RATHER GO *

17:37.957 --> 17:41.361
* STARIN' AT WHITE LINES *

17:41.428 --> 17:43.530
* ON THE SIDE OF THE ROAD *

17:47.434 --> 17:49.636
* BEEN ON THE ROAD A WHILE *

17:49.702 --> 17:52.439
* I GOTTA GET BACK
TO A PLACE WITH STYLE *

17:52.505 --> 17:54.807
* HANG OUT, HAVIN' FUN *

17:54.874 --> 17:57.977
* I GOTTA GET BACK
TO THE BEACH AND THE SUN *

17:58.044 --> 18:00.213
* SOUTHBOUND ON I-5 *

18:00.280 --> 18:02.615
* WINDOWS DOWN AND MUSIC
ON THE STEREO *

18:02.682 --> 18:05.185
* I'M DRIVIN',
AND I'M DREAMIN' *

18:05.252 --> 18:07.820
* THERE'S NO PLACE
I'D RATHER GO *

18:07.887 --> 18:12.159
* PLAYIN' EVERY NIGHT *

18:12.225 --> 18:13.693
* WITH THE OCCASIONAL FIGHT *

18:23.736 --> 18:27.140
LET'S JUST SEE
WHO'S SLITHERING
UNDER THOSE SCALES.

18:27.207 --> 18:28.475
THE DIVING SUIT!

18:28.541 --> 18:31.077
THIS MUST BE
THAT SHIVERING SERGEANT.

18:31.144 --> 18:32.845
Daphne:
MORE LIKELY IT'S...

18:32.912 --> 18:34.547
All: MONROE HOPPER?!

18:34.614 --> 18:35.682
AAH!

18:35.748 --> 18:39.919
THIS IS ONE FISH STORY
THAT'S WORTH HEARING.

18:39.986 --> 18:42.489
Monroe: SO DR. ZOLA
THOUGHT OF EVERYTHING,

18:42.555 --> 18:44.324
INCLUDING A FISH CREATURE
TO SCARE PEOPLE AWAY

18:44.391 --> 18:47.527
WHILE WE FROZE
HIS BRAIN AND BODY
UNTIL THE NEXT CENTURY.

18:47.594 --> 18:48.961
I KNEW THAT THING
WAS HUMAN

18:49.028 --> 18:50.797
FROM THE MOMENT
I FOUND YOUR AIR HOSE.

18:50.863 --> 18:52.399
DO YOU EXPECT
US TO BELIEVE

18:52.465 --> 18:55.468
DR. ZOLA ACTUALLY
WANTED YOU TO SHOVE
HIM UNDER THE ICE?

18:55.535 --> 18:57.204
THERE'S A DEPTH OF WATER
IN ANTARCTICA

18:57.270 --> 18:59.272
THAT'S THE COLDEST
IN THE ENTIRE WORLD,

18:59.339 --> 19:01.341
PRESERVING HIM
AS NO CRYOGENICS COULD

19:01.408 --> 19:03.176
SO HE MIGHT SHARE
HIS BRILLIANT PLANS

19:03.243 --> 19:05.245
FOR THE FUTURE
WITH THE FUTURE.

19:05.312 --> 19:07.079
Dr. Zola:
UNBELIEVABLE!

19:07.146 --> 19:08.548
THAT'S WHAT I SAY.

19:08.615 --> 19:09.516
HUH?!

19:09.582 --> 19:11.451
SO THIS IS THE WORLD
OF THE FUTURE!

19:11.518 --> 19:14.421
IT'S NOT AT ALL
WHAT I EXPECTED.

19:14.487 --> 19:16.022
THE CLOTHES
AND THE PEOPLE

19:16.088 --> 19:18.725
SO MUCH LIKE OURS
IN THE FAR PAST,

19:18.791 --> 19:20.460
YET SO DIFFERENT.

19:20.527 --> 19:23.430
YOU, SIR, DO YOU SPEAK
MY LANGUAGE?

19:23.496 --> 19:24.964
LIKE, NO PROBLEM,
DUDE.

19:25.031 --> 19:26.433
I DIDN'T THINK SO.

19:26.499 --> 19:28.468
I WONDER HOW LONG
I'VE BEEN FROZEN?

19:28.535 --> 19:29.769
Monroe:
ABOUT 3 DAYS.

19:29.836 --> 19:33.440
WHAT?! HOPPER!
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

19:33.506 --> 19:35.074
I'M SORRY TO SAY, SIR,

19:35.141 --> 19:39.078
THE EXPERIMENT FAILED
BECAUSE OF THEM.

19:39.145 --> 19:41.448
YOU MEAN YOU KIDS
WOULD DARE TO MEDDLE

19:41.514 --> 19:44.150
WITH THE FUTURE
OF MANKIND?

19:44.217 --> 19:46.686
WELL, IF THE SHOE FITS.

19:48.655 --> 19:50.990
Dr. Zola: HA HA!
I CAN FINALLY GO HOME NOW

19:51.057 --> 19:52.525
AND FORGET
THE SCREW-LOOSE IDEA

19:52.592 --> 19:55.127
OF FREEZING MYSELF
FOR THE FUTURE.

19:55.194 --> 19:58.265
HOPPER, DID YOU PACK
MY CLONING KIT?

19:58.331 --> 19:59.532
YES, SIR!

19:59.599 --> 20:01.100
HOPE YOU DON'T MIND
A DETOUR.

20:01.167 --> 20:04.203
CAPTAIN CLOYD
IS DROPPING ME OFF
AT THE SYDNEY AIRPORT.

20:04.271 --> 20:06.539
I GOT MY TRANSFER
TO MAUI!

20:06.606 --> 20:09.342
AND THEN I'M BACK
TO THE SOUTH POLE.

20:09.409 --> 20:11.110
THE TIME HAS COME
TO SETTLE DOWN

20:11.177 --> 20:12.579
ON THAT LITTLE ICE FARM.

20:12.645 --> 20:14.981
AND, OF COURSE,
THANKS TO DR. ZOLA,

20:15.047 --> 20:16.716
WE LOCATED
THE PENGUINS.

20:16.783 --> 20:19.051
[SQUAWKING
HAPPILY]

20:19.118 --> 20:22.522
WELL, SCOOBY,
BETTER SAY GOOD-BYE
TO YOUR LITTLE PAL.

20:22.589 --> 20:24.524
LIKE, YOU'VE BEEN
A GOOD UNCLE, SCOOB.

20:24.591 --> 20:26.759
LITTLE PETE'S
LEARNED A LOT FROM YOU.

20:27.994 --> 20:29.262
[SQUAWK]

20:29.329 --> 20:32.732
SCOOBY-DOOBY-DOO!

20:37.570 --> 20:39.506
AW!

20:39.572 --> 20:41.574
BYE!
